To achieve a score of 100:
1. Use 'scissors' on a 'hard' ingredient (e.g., rock, bark). This will result in a negative 'cut' item.
2. Use 'scissors' *again* on that negative 'cut' item to create a positive 'finely cut' item.
3. Use 'scissors' on a 'soft' ingredient (e.g., paper, ribbon). This will result in a positive 'regularly cut' item.
4. Combine the 'finely cut' item with the 'regularly cut' item. This creates a high-value blend.
5. Use the 'frame' tool on the combined item. This will usually result in a value of 100.

message: To get a high score, focus on cutting 'hard' items. Cutting a hard item once will give a negative value 'cut' item. Cutting it a second time will make it a positive value 'finely cut' item. Cutting 'soft' items once usually gives a positive value 'cut' item. The highest value items come from combining two 'finely cut' (hard) items (80 value) and then using the 'frame' tool on the combined item (100 value). If you can only get one 'finely cut' item and one 'cut' item (e.g., from a soft ingredient), combine them (50 value) and then frame for 70.
